Caption:
Happy Friday Friends!
.
Here’s a quick reminder that progress is going to ebb and flow with any fitness goal. That’s why it’s so important to start that journey from a place of love and respect for your body at every size. Losing too fast can cause rebound, pushing too hard in the gym can cause injury. Remember that slow and steady wins the race. If you hit a plateau, make small adjustments to see more change. Be patient with the process and with yourself. It’s not necessary to be thin to be happy. So don’t wait. Enjoy life now and all throughout the journey!
.
Don’t forget to stop by tomorrow for “Ask me anything” Saturday!
.
Always remember...
.
Your worth has nothing to do with your weight. Love and respect yourself. Enjoy life and be happy.💖
.
For coaching inquiries, email me at GetHappyBeFit@gmail.com

A frequent phrase for me is “an object in motion tends to stay in motion and an object at rest tends to stay at rest.” That doesn’t mean I have to be the fastest or the strongest or the best at any of the activities I enjoy - but I have to keep going. 
A friend recently asked about how to “get back on” the workout train. My suggestions? @onepeloton fun walks or restorative yoga. There are great classes available for free on YouTube! Restorative yoga is like a nap/ stretch combo but gets me present in my body and more prepared for movement.

Dieses Mal hatten wir etwas mehr Freizeit und die Möglichkeit auch die eher weniger bekannten Straßen zu erkunden. Natürlich sind die berühmten Fotomotive wie der Broadway, der Times Square, Central park  und die Brooklyn Bridge usw es absolut wert zu besuchen... New York bietet aber so unglaublich viel mehr. Ich kann jedem empfehlen sich von typischen advisern abzukapseln und einfach auf eigene Faust zu erkunden. .
.

Caption:
No one is you and that is your power ✨ 
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
This week I had a day where I doubted everything I did and started to compare myself to others and it made me feel so rubbish. 
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
I took a step back and opened up to a good friend about how I was feeling and she helped me put myself right and remember that comparing your life/journey to someone else’s gets you nowhere.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
We often lose our way when we compare ourselves to others but remember, you are unique and what makes you perfectly different is what sets you aside to achieve your goals.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
When you’re having a shit day, be gentle to yourself, stay positive, show gratitude, show compassion and remind yourself that you are special and needed here 🤎 
.

.
.
.
.
.
.

Caption:
La riserva naturale del biotopo Fontanazzo 👇🏼

📌 Ci si arriva percorrendo la statale 47 della Valsugana fino all'uscita per Grigno; due chilometri e si è al paese: passato il semaforo, si va avanti ancora duecento metri, poi si svolta a destra, in direzione Selva di Grigno. 
La strada continua per oltre due chilometri, sempre in direzione di Selva: il biotopo Fontanazzo è sulla destra.

🌿 Comprende prati, coltivi, lembi di foresta alluvionale di ontano nero, ontano bianco, salice bianco, frassino e tratti di bosco ripariale. 
Nonchè il fiume e il greto fluviale, oltre a corsi d'acqua minori.

🦎 Nel fitto della vegetazione trovano possibilità di rifugio, alimentazione e riproduzione numerose specie di mammiferi e di uccelli quali l'airone cenerino, il merlo acquaiolo e lo splendido martin pescatore. I corsi d'acqua e le risorgive all'interno del Biotopo presentano specie ittiche d'elevato valore come lo Scazzone, la rarissima Lampreda padana e il Gambero di fiume. 

🏞 Uno tra i maggiori motivi di interesse naturalistico del Biotopo Fontanazzo è costituito dal suo particolare sistema idrico: la zona protetta infatti comprende alcune importanti sorgenti di fondovalle che sono in diretta comunicazione con il complesso carsico delle grotte della Bigonda e del Calgeron, che si aprono sul versante destro della valle a poca distanza dal Biotopo.

#grigno

Today I’m thankful for being able to do what I love. The acting industry is still mostly shut down, but I’ve had such amazing opportunities in the last couple of years, and also working in the health and fitness industry is so fulfilling. Watching people find love for themselves and their bodies while reaching goals they never thought they could makes my heart soar.
.
What are you thankful for today?
.
If you want to start the journey to self love while taking it to the next level with your weight loss and fitness, or if you feel like you’ve tried everything and nothing works, check out my podcast Get Happy Be Fit. It’s available on all podcast platforms. Or you can email me for coaching inquiries!
.
Always remember...
.
Your worth has nothing to do with your weight. Love and respect yourself. Enjoy life and be happy.💖

Caption:
🍫 DOUBLE CHOCOLATE OREO BROWNIES RECIPE 🍫
•
Follow along with these steps to make your very own fudgy brownies with extra Oreo crunchiness 🤤 make sure you save this post so you can come back to the recipe later!
•
225g plain chocolate
225g unsalted butter
3 eggs
225g caster sugar
2 tablespoons black coffee
75g self-raising flour
Pinch of salt
200g white chocolate chips
5ml vanilla essence or extract
2 x 154g packet of Oreos
•
1. Preheat your oven 180c/160c fan/gas mark 5. Line a 13" x 9" tin with greaseproof paper
2. Break the plain chocolate into a heatproof bowl with the butter. Set the bowl over a pan of barely simmering water and leave for 5-10 minutes, stirring occasionally until the mixture is melted and smooth. You could also do this in the microwave, taking care not to burn the chocolate. Remove the bowl from the pan and leave to cool for 5 minutes 🍫🧈
3. In a separate bowl, beat the eggs, sugar and coffee until smooth, then gradually beat in the cooled melted chocolate mixture 🥚☕️
4. Sift the flour and salt over the mixture, then fold in together with the white chocolate chips and vanilla extract
5. In a small bowl, empty one packet of Oreos. Use the handle of a rolling pin or wooden spoon to break the biscuits up in to chunks, taking care not to make them too small 🍪
6. Pour half the mixture into the prepared tin and spread it right to the edges. Add the broken Oreos over the top, then cover with the remaining mixture. Spread it out with the back of a spoon, then use the whole Oreos from your other packet to decorate the top
7. Pop the tin into the oven and bake for around 35-40 minutes or until just firm in the centre. You won't want to bake it for too much longer than this, as your brownies will be dry
8. Remove your brownie slab from the oven and leave it to cool fully in the tin before turning it out and slicing the whole thing into bars or squares 🍫
•
This is a super easy and ridiculously delicious recipe, so give it a go and share your brownie photos with me 🥰💛

Caption:
Happy Tuesday Friends!
.
My freckles practically disappear until summer. I’ve been in the sun a lot so they are making their seasonal entrance!
.
I used to HATE my freckles. It took me a long time to own them and appreciate them. Now I love them and get excited when they make an appearance. Last year one of my followers told me I should get them laser removed because it would make me more “charming”. 🤦🏼‍♀️ You’re never going to be everyone’s cup of tea. The important thing is how YOU feel about yourself. So today I’m celebrating my freckle face.
.
Always remember...
.
Your worth has nothing to do with your weight. (Or your face) Love and respect yourself. Enjoy life and be happy.💖

Caption:
☕️ I’m always going on about how much I love going out for cake and coffee, but I feel like I need to come clean... I don’t actually like coffee 😱 I’m so sorry! It makes me panicky and anxious, and it doesn’t taste amazing 😳 please forgive me!
•
Instead, I’m all about a hot chocolate - the more marshmallows and squirty cream, the better 🍫 this particular hot choc from @paticake.patisserie was unbelievably good and it was the perfect after dinner treat. It was just begging for a biscuit accompaniment for dunking! 🍪

Hazelnuts- lighly roasted
Dates
Coconut oil
Cocoa powder

Pinch of pink salt

Caption: Short exposure\ud83d\udcf8\ud83d\udca5\ud83c\udf09\ud83c\udf09\nBalancing getting enough light at night yet details of fast moving clouds without smudging them is quite a tricky mix of wider aperture and usable not too high iso with a short shutter. That night the cloud details above #TowerBridge where too pretty to just smudge them with 30sec exposure so I used these settings instead the preserve them:\n\ud83d\udcf8 @hasselblad_official #X1D50c \ud83d\udd2d 90mm f3.2 \ud83c\udf9b F5, iso 100, 4secs

Caption: Daytime smudger\ud83d\udcf88stop screw on ND 82mm does come handy and is most of the time in my bag. I rarely do this long exposures but use it to shoot 1-2s shutter timelapses at f4-8 thus avoiding dust spot yet getting all the smoothness of long exposure. And after the timelapse is done, I close to f16 and go 25-30s for a single shot like this \ud83d\udc4d\ud83c\udffbKilling two birds with one stone\ud83d\ude01

Caption:
Distance compression 🔭🔎🌃
Now this is quite a bit outside London, but it's an iconic place, and no, it's not a Ferrari garage as it would've been red, so...
➡️Can you tell what did I compress this time just below Canary Wharf❓❓
____
Shot a few years ago with a Panasonic GH2 and some old manual cheap ebayed 400mm lens that I just can't remember the name of, but as you know on a 2x crop body, this was around 800mm and I've probably cropped it in edit a bit too.
____
‼️🙌🏻Location answer update🙌🏻‼️
It was taken from Ebbsfleet Valley, the next garden city project just outside the M25, between Dartford and Gravesend, some houses and flats being built there will possibly enjoy this view. The horse projection was of @bluewatershopping centre logo on a wall of the quarry that it's it, you'd probably see it if you ever drove to Bluewater in the evening. Camera to Canary Wharf distance circa 15 miles .
____

Caption:
One thing I’ve done differently this year is make more time for mobility, stretching, recovery and restorative yoga. I can feel a difference in my joints. I bounce back from a run faster and with less pain. It’s basically the adult equivalent of actually flossing every day. Plus you don’t have to wear a sports bra or workout clothes. As we welcome May I’m taking the time to reflect. 
This time last year I had just finished uni and was getting ready to go backpacking. I had a rollercoaster of a year after that. My best friend died in my arms, someone close to me was suicidal and then I jetted off to Thailand. Whilst away I fulfilled so many of my dreams but I did so with a heavy heart and I felt lost. 
Fast forward to this year and now we’re all in a pandemic and life feels as though it’s been put on hold. However, I’ve taken the time this morning to set myself some goals for this month and appreciate where I am in life. 
I was so lost at the start of the year, everything felt too much and I simply couldn’t cope - even whilst I was away travelling. It was as if everything was pointless and that there was no meaning to life. 
Nevertheless, I’m grateful for those times as it’s lead me to where I am now. I learned some hard lessons and now I’m a little wiser and a lot more full of love. 
It doesn’t mean that I don’t have days where I am low or that my life is without it’s problems but, do you know what? I’ll take the bad days any day of the week because without the lows you can’t have the highs, and life is so god damn magical. 
In life we will always have problems, it doesn’t matter how trivial or catastrophic they are, they never go away but it’s up to us to see the good in things. No ones life is as they expected right now and that’s okay. Things never turn out as you expect anyway so we may as well let go of expectations. Instead, focus on the now and how we can make today count. 
I’ve set myself some things to work on over this month and at the start of June I want to reflect to see what’s changed in that time. A short little month out of a long life. Already this year so much has changed for me. I am in a much better head space and I feel fulfilled. 
I understand that this is a difficult time for many people (myself included) but it will pass, things will get better. It is easier said than done but please don’t let life slip you by, even in a pandemic. It’s too precious.

Caption:
Hey you beautiful people. Today has been a pretty packed day. Also I have to admit that I was going through the second day of not really getting into a flow. EVEN MORE IMPORTANT THAT I SHARE THIS WITH ALL OF YOU. Every single person who is following me sees me starting my day smiling and drinking my oat milk cappuccino. Hundreds of thousands are watching me every week getting out of bed —most of the time unfiltered and just how I look after I woke up. I receive so many DMs from all over the world just saying “thank you for giving me this smile every morning” And now I wanted to say something about this... I love you— not for consuming my content but for taking the time to let me know that you get what I am trying to do. I try to keep routines and share positive vibes. I try to send a smile and motivate more people to not loose hope or drive. Here in Germany we are still going through a hard time and I know it’s still everywhere the case. Back to what I wanted to say— I am not always motivated... I am not always in a good mood and for sure I am not always unconcerned. BUT I try to do my best... for me and for all the people in my environment or everybody who needs me. This gives me passion, freedom and hope... and the best thing about that is that it keeps me busy and healthy 💪🏼☺️ please take care ♥️ Don’t forget that TOGETHER WE ARE STRONG and everybody can share a smile and make someone’s day so easy. I promise tomorrow I’ll give y’all another smile 😊 
Love 
Angelo 
.
.
.
.

Caption:
I always had a creative voice which always longed and searched for opportunities to express itself ! 
But fears and limiting mindsets would always stop me from expressing myself completely! 
It had been years ,ever since I joined a 9-5 job, that I had completely lost my creative side... I was caught in a rut repeating the same mechanical routine day in and day out!
Life experiences and emotional trauma however brought me back to my creative side !! 
I started finding solace in expressing myself and my voice, the way I wanted ...
Constant isolation during this pandemic affected year brought me closer to myself and made my creative voice stronger than never before ....
I am on a path of growing stronger , loving myself and healing like you.
This journey of self discovery is quite amazing I must say...
.
This picture is taken from 2 months back from the mirror series...
.
#selfdiscovery #healing #selfcare

Caption: Any one else feeling like they\u2019re on a journey of self discovery whilst in lockdown? I feel like I\u2019ve had the time to really connect with myself as well as learn to live in the moment. I appreciate that for some this isolation is difficult either emotionally and/or financially but we have to admit that there has been a great sense of community. I think it\u2019s because we are all experiencing this together. We are all in the same boat and maybe it\u2019s making us feel less alone. It is a shared problem. A talking point, even. Despite being physically isolated, people are actually coming together in unity. People are clapping on their doorsteps for the NHS, smiling and thanking each other as they cross the street, local communities and neighbours are delivering food to the vulnerable, people are finally spending time with their loved ones and we are appreciating the hard workers that are showing up everyday, selling us our toilet roll or collecting our rubbish. I for one am ever so grateful right now. Not to mention that there is so much peace and quiet \ud83e\udd2b Be safe \ud83d\ude37#socialisolation

Caption:
Anxiety is horrid. But being a person prone to the deep sensitivity anxiety entails can also mean that you develop curiosity, you feel art deeply, you disappear into books like other lives, your sexual imagination becomes wilder, foods become heightened, songs can make you cry or burst with life. Anxiety is the flip side of intensity, of feeling, and feeling can be f* good.⁣
(@mattzhaig )⁣
⁣
..and talking about feelings and emotions should never end up as an argument.⁣
you are NOT exaggerating and you are NOT blowing things out of proportion.⁣
You feel how you feel and what you feel and that's ALWAYS ok ❤️⁣
⁣
⁣
⁣

Caption: Happy Thankful Thursday! My most recent podcast episode is all about how making a conscious effort to be grateful will change your life for the better. Today I\u2019m thankful for coffee and quiet mornings before the hustle and bustle of the day begins. What are you thankful for today? Caption:
You aren’t ready until you’re ready. 5 years ago I started the process of making over my life. I took a half pay cut leaving my career as an executive assistant to C level executives to move into HR. The pay cut hurt. I’d learned to enjoy my comfortable salary - but I wasn’t happy. I knew I needed to pivot to get into HR but no one would hire me for higher level positions with comparable salaries. So I made the leap and took a role as a HR admin at a great company. I worked hard. I built relationships. I absorbed everything. I got certifications. I was promoted. 
I’ve learned that most growth and change is not linear. It’s a winding path of ups and downs and your path is going to be truly unique. That’s what’s exciting. ✨💕✨

Caption:
I was going to write “don’t let tomorrows pain take from today” after receiving some sad news regarding my best friend and brother. He has terminal cancer. 
Anyone effected by cancer will know that you could spend hours thinking yourself crazy with the endless possibilities of what the future might look like. Likewise for many of life’s curveballs. 
All that this does is impair our perception and dampen our gratitude. It doesn’t change anything. 
However, on the flip side this is also true when we “look forward” to things. In doing so we forget to appreciate this very moment that we are living in. 
Whilst on holiday in the Highlands last week, kayaking and paddle boarding on Loch Morlich (Britain’s only fresh water beach which looks as though you’re in Canada 😍) I found myself thinking “I can’t wait to do this in South East Asia when I go in September”. No, that was the wrong outlook. I quickly reminded myself that actually, the moment was perfect just as it was. 
So instead I want to write “today is a good day to have a good day”. You just have to be grateful and live for the moment. 
Put into perspective; today, I still get to spend time with my brother and I am grateful that I have the opportunity to show him how much he is loved and, that actually, my time in the Highlands was just as great as my trip to Asia will be. 
By living in the moment and having gratitude, today will always be a good day even when tomorrow is uncertain.

Many peoples hearts are breaking right now, but together we find comfort in each other.

Caption:
This is a REAL smile ! And here is why 👇🏼
People keep asking me “Angelo, are you happy with your life?” My answer is ALWAYS “yes dude I always am” and they are like “yes but you don’t have a girlfriend and you live and work in a fake society isn’t that hard?”.... My key points of being happy with and in my life are not related to any society or a girlfriend. Ofc it would be nice to be in love with a woman and having a beautiful #instacouplegoals relationship but Dude these relationships are rare unfortunately. Ofc I would love to live in a real society with just genuine people but for real “NAME ONE” 🤷🏻‍♂️ My facts are. 
-My family, my friends and myself are healthy. 
-I get challenged quite a lot so I don’t rest at the same point.
-Nobody tells me what to do.
-I am able to create and organize my days just how I want them to be.
-I am independent.
-I help other people.
-I travel the world.
-I don’t have any financial problems.
-I AM NOT DONE YET 😎
What I want to say is “it’s not about what you COULD HAVE it’s about NOW AND WHAT YOU ALREADY ACHIEVED. I feel like a lot of people just try to reach goals but they forget that there is always a way to reach and achieve them. The real skill is being happy and balanced ALL THE WAY THROUGH ☀️ I wish y’all a fabulous Tuesday ♥️😘 
.
.
.

Caption:
Swipe ⬅️ to see Merry’s first ever trip to a UK sea side 🏖 🌊 

I’m bursting with pride with the progress Merry has made. Merry was once so scared that she was afraid of her own shadow. I remember when she first arrived with us at the RSPCA South Godstone and attempting to take her for a walk. Merry literally clung to the floor and froze on the spot because she was that frightened. Everyday things that we take for granted was a challenge for her. So to think that she could hop in a car for a day out down the beach is mind blowing 🤯

We aren’t certain of her past but we know she was shipped over from Romania where she was living as a street dog and the charity who had brought her over left her living in a barren cage, too small for her to even turn around in. We also think that she was kicked at some point as our vets found evidence of trauma to her spleen 🥺 It’s no wonder she found life scary, really. 

Her rehabilitation has been a long journey. We’ve had to help her unlearn her traumatic past and show her a brighter future. Merry is still apprehensive about meeting new people and other animals (which is why she has to be muzzled in public) but we have taught her some essential life skills to enable her to take life in her stride. 

Seeing her walking along the beach front like a normal dog and getting to witness her face light up when sharing my food is priceless. It reminds me that my purpose in life and as a behaviourist is to help these animals. To fight for them and be their voice.

Working with rescue dogs is really tough. You get battered and bruised and your heart gets broken and torn into two. You go home tired and upset for the damage that is done to dogs like Merry. We work weekends, bank holidays, Christmas and New Year. We get bitten, pulled around and scratched. It is even really quite scary at times. It is not a job for the faint hearted. 

But do you know what? Every second of the self sacrifice that comes with job is worth it. Nothing beats sending one of your dogs off to their new home or seeing the joy on their faces as they start to leave their past behind them. 

🌟 continued in comments 🌟

Caption: Happy Friday Friends! Does anyone else have pets that will not leave them alone when they\u2019re trying to workout? When all this is over, let\u2019s remember not to take the simple, seemingly annoying things like going to work, standing in long lines and invasive little pups for granted. Have an amazing weekend everyone!

It's been nearly two weeks since Kipper passed away, but going for walks with Purd(ita) has made things a little more bearable. -

No other dog could ever be the same as Kipper, but as a dog owner for thirteen years it's very hard to shake the habits you have: putting on a baby-dog voice, going for long walks with a trusty companion, and stealing a cuddle when you're feeling not-so-good (with a cold, in my case). -

So here's to my Kipper - gone but never forgotten; and to Purdy - a furry friend when I needed it most!

Caption:
I’ve been talking to myself lately and saying, “I love my body” x10 times a day. 
I’ve been struggling and frustrated lately with my fitness journey. I took a break from tracking my macros for a few weeks. My weight stayed the same. I’ve been focused on getting better quality sleep for the past few months and my weight stayed the same. I hired a nutritionist to watch everything I eat and give me feedback and still my weight stayed the same. Then I went to Prague. 
I walked 7 miles a day and didn’t eat for 2 days after a bad case of food intolerance. I lost 5 pounds. 🙄😆🤷🏼‍♀️Working through self love while on a health and fitness journey can be really tricky.  Sometimes you just have to say it until you believe it and I feel like it’s working. 🌸✨🍑

Caption:
On Cloud 9 ☁️
.
.
So I tried the Starbucks Ariana Grande inspired “Cloud Macchiato” and thought I’d give a quick review 💌
.
I’m going to start by being honest, I don’t really like iced coffee (but for the aesthetic you know 🤷🏼‍♀️)
.
It’s very much in 2 separate parts - The “cloud” part is super light and fluffy, doesn’t really have a great deal of taste, literally just a sort of creamy froth (I’m a froth fan so this is a plus in my book) .
The coffee part is just cold coffee (yes, im aware that’s what an iced coffee is but I’m strictly a latte girl so this doesn’t suit my agenda)
.
I’m not really sure how the parts are supposed to be consumed (does this make me uncultured or just severely out of touch?) so I decided to mix it all up together (yes like a 5 year old) which made it lose any cloudiness and it ended up as a standard iced coffee with a slight caramel taste .
Overall I’d give it a 4/10 and would say this definitely would not be as popular if it didn’t have Ariana’s name associated with it (good move Starbucks) ☕️

Caption: Every perception is individual and interpreted differently ... it is impressive when you think about how many people are there to make something work anyway. We duel, measure our strength, compare ourselves, get the lead when we run out of arguments and look questioningly and enviously at our neighbor, where the grass is always much greener than in our garden. There is nothing impossible anymore ... for none of us. I am a part of this \u201cintermediate generation\u201d that grown up without internet and colored TV. When I was a little boy, my father taught me how to transfer a song from the radio to one of my sister\u2019s bibi blocksberg cassettes using a bread knife and sellotape. If I woke up too early in the morning, the test pattern was still running in the TV channel. Somehow suddenly everything developed so fast ... with the internet, all the doors of this world are opened ... suddenly we are all connected and can share everything with each other ... my generation knows exactly what I\u2019m talking about. To all the others, I just want to say that it is always a privilege to be so closely connected ... so use this to do good things.\nIt\u2019s easy to find a talent everywhere now ... but that doesn\u2019t mean it\u2019s less worth now.

Day 1——> Day 13 #progress #75hard 
#75hardchallenge 

I’ve made the decision that I’m not going to talk publicly about weight loss details on here. If you want to talk numbers and are respectful we can talk in my DMs. I’m making this choice because while I started out with a goal of losing weight a few years ago a lot of things I’ve changed for me since then. I want to be strong. I want to be able to hike long and strenuous hikes. I want to be able to run and chase and play with my nieces. I don’t care as much about a number on the scale anymore. I like to know how my clothes feel and the amount of energy I have day to day. 

I didn’t sign up for this as a weight loss challenge. I signed up because I needed more structure in my day while working from home. I signed up because I want to improve my relationship with alcohol and find other ways to celebrate, grieve and pass the time. #bodypositivity #bodypositivemovement #bodypositive #transformationtuesday #beforeandafter #andyfrisella  #75hardresults #plussizefitness #sobercurious #plussizefitnessjourney #plussizefit

Caption:
Ich werde so oft von euch, meinen Freunden oder meiner Familie gefragt wieso ich keine Freundin habe... ich bin nie umfangreich darauf eingegangen und mittlerweile bin ich euch allen ja fast schon eine Erklärung schuldig. Es gibt keinen allgemeinen Grund dafür, ich liebe Frauen und es gibt wirklich sehr viele die mir rein äußerlich gut gefallen. Ich möchte eine Frau, die ihr eigenes Leben lebt, die sich nicht für mich aufgibt. Ich möchte eine Frau, die loyal und treu ist auch wenn es gerade vllt mal nicht die heile Welt ist. Ich möchte eine Bereicherung sein und kein Umstand. Ich habe mal zu einer Frau gesagt „ich brauch dich“ und direkt danach erkannt, dass dies der grundlegend falsche Ansatz ist. Sich abhängig zu machen schränkt ein. Du musst dich selbst brauchen, glücklich dabei sein und erst dann kannst du eine Beziehung mit positiver Energie füllen. Ich möchte eine Frau die mich fordert, überrascht und zum Lachen bringt. Ich brauche keine Schminke, keine Highheels und keinen Klunker... ich brauch jemand echten, der mit sich selbst zufrieden ist und nicht nach etwas sucht, was gut passen könnte... Ich möchte mein Herz vergeben und nicht meinen Status. .
I am so often asked by you, my friends or my family why I don’t have a girlfriend ... I have never dealt with it extensively and now I almost owe you all an explanation. There is no general reason for that, I love women and there are really many that I like in appearance. I want a woman who lives her own life, who doesn’t give herself up for me. I want a woman who is loyal, even if it's just not the perfect world sometimes. I want to be an enrichment and not a circumstance. I once said to a woman "I need you" and immediately realized that this is the fundamentally wrong approach. To be dependent restricts a relationship. You have to like yourself, be happy and only then you are able to fill a relationship with positive energy. I want a woman who is challenging me, surprises me and makes me laugh. I don’t need make-up, highheels, or jewelry... I need someone real, who is happy from within and is not looking for something that just would fit well ... I want to give my heart and not my status.
.
#angelocarlucci

Caption:
Happy Monday Friend!
.
In this week’s episode of Get Happy Be Fit I talk about the best way to workout for sustainable weight loss and the benefits of building muscle along with the misconceptions a lot of women have about weight training.
.
A lot of us feel like we have to completely overhaul our lives in one fell swoop, do insane amounts of cardio and be in the gym every day. But what we really should be doing is working smarter, not harder. The minimum effect dose is all you need to see results and create sustainable weight loss over time.
.
Get Happy Be Fit is available on all podcast platforms or you can check my story for a link to download on ITunes.
.
Always remember...
.
Your worth has nothing to do with your weight. Love and respect yourself. Enjoy life and be happy.💖

Caption: From silly to not quite pro, bit a little bit less silly\ud83d\ude02What am I talking about ? Well....back in Dec 2015 I bought a \u00a330 telescopic radio mast and decided to mount a GoPro on it, go to #WestminsterBridge and get a few shots like this above of #BigBen \ud83d\udd70 Despite my best efforts to carry it out safe, the way it looked (the mast and me) it could\u2019ve been easily mistaken for a bazooka or a threat to national security\ud83d\ude02I\u2019m surprised I didn\u2019t get shot doing this that day\ud83e\udd23But then I\u2019m sure the authorities have a decent zoom on their cctv so they could see what that idiot is doing\ud83e\udd26\ud83c\udffc\u200d\u2642\ufe0fAnyway, these shots did incredibly well, sold a few, opened some brand partnerships yet... I\u2019ve not done this again since as I wasn\u2019t happy about the safety measures of this setup. I searched pro photo masts and prices in excess of \u00a31,000, and size requiring a truck to transport it didn\u2019t feel me with confidence I could do this ever again. That brings me onto the announcement that yesterday at The Photography Show I have now acquired a reasonably priced professional (looking at least) telescopic mast that will reduce the chances of me getting shot in the future while actually safely taking a payload of a mirrorless body with a wide angle lens (I hope), not just a GoPro. Exciting times, can\u2019t wait to do this again in even better quality now\ud83e\udd29\ud83c\udfd7\ud83d\udcf8

Caption:
For all German speakers check my story 😊 
Happy Monday to you! I hope you’ve had a GREAT weekend!😎
.
So…where to begin? On last Thursday’s video, I told you about The Movember Foundation and how I decided to get involved in it and support the reason behind it, Men’s Health. How? Just Keep reading 🤓
.
The Movember Foundation has been raising funds for research and health services for the last 15 years, targeting prostate and testicular cancers, mental health and suicide prevention. 🖤
.

What have they achieved?
.
✔Growing a community of “Mo Bros” and “Mo Sistas”  from 30 mustaches to 5 million worldwide. And still counting!
✔Raising €55M last year. Reaching an overall of €650M! .
I am proud to announce that I have become a “Mo Bro”! 🧔🏻 If you wish, you can support the cause donating money through my profile. 👆🏻 (LINK IN MY BIO) 👆🏻
.
Furthermore, it is as important to raise awareness to help preventing these health issues from happening, and help us men live longer. To get you involved, we decided to make A CONTEST! 💥💥💥
. What can you do? ➡Post a picture featuring your mustaches and beards, and by the end of the week, I’ll share the best ones! 📷
.
- The most creative beard/mustache (Girls, you can get creative too!💁‍♀)
- The most beards and mustaches in one picture (Team up with your fathers, grandpas & friends) - The longest beard/ mustache! .
Don’t forget to tag me and use the following Movember Hashtags on our posts: 
#Movember #movember2018 #movemberfoundation @angelocarlucci #angelocarlucci 
Thank you and GOOD LUCK !!🍀💛

Caption:
Hello #London skyline lovers🇬🇧🌆😍
➡️ #WWIM12_UpInLondon ⬅️
Everyone knows this weekend is #WWIM12 and there's going to be plenty of groups of photographers meeting shooting together all around the city, from the street to the rivers, up on the roofs and down in the underground... and you know which ones I like😊 oh yes, the ones with good views and what better viewpoint to start the day than @shardview 🔝 So I've teamed up with The View from the Shard to organise a small #meetup at their #BestViewInLondon viewing platform. Meetup is free but spaces are limited. There will be 6 spots up for grabs. The RSVPs will open at the same time ( tomorrow at 9pm ) for everyone, so whoever is quickest, gets in. Please only RSVP yes if you're definitely sure you can attend. Join my group on Meetup.com ( ➡️link in bio ) and will will see the seven of you on Saturday morning. 😀😀😀😀😀😀😀
After this morning meetup, I will be going to Avi's ( @gcooler ) meetup at 12.15 and in the evening to José's ( @jlds.photography ) night session, so I hope to meet most, if not all of you throughout the day in line with Instagram's #WWIM12 theme of #todayimet which will follow by #whoifollow 🌇🌆🇬🇧🌆🌃🔝🇬🇧
See you soon🙌🏻😉 Michael

Caption:
2014. Long hours sitting at a desk at a job I thought I “should be doing”. Snacking on chips, cookies, sandwiches and whatever was free around the office. Long commute on a train sitting. Leaving work and coming home in the dark for over half the year. Sitting on a couch and watching TV most nights. Drinking and eating out a lot. Repeat. 2019. Consistency. Vitamin D. Fruits, Veggies, lean Protein. Challenging Workouts. Podcasts. Books. A job I love. Challenging myself mentally by going back to school. Expanding my social circle. Making new friends who like all the things I enjoy now. 
The whole notion of “it’s not a diet it’s a lifestyle change” is so true but I wish more people would show what that really looks like. That’s why I made my Instagram public! Please tag more real people that are doing this the healthy and authentic way below so I can continue to build this network!! •

Caption:
This weekend at the Power Her Potential conference someone asked about confidence. 
How do you get yourself to a place of confidence when you aren’t feeling your best? 🤔
When I’m really struggling to feel my best, I like to meet myself in the middle working from both the inside and out. The inside can mean taking a yoga class to meditate, focus on my breath and ignore any negative self talk.  I also have a gratitude journal I write in to remember my blessings or go back to my #30daysofgratitude list. 
From the outside, I am always one good Epsom salt bath or manicure away from a better mood. 🙏🏻

Caption:
Happy Monday Friends!
.
I stepped away from social media a bit the past couple of weeks. Like so many people I felt that what was going on in the world deserved the attention of all of us and I didn’t want to take away from that.
.
During times like this I REALLY struggle with my mental health. In this week’s episode of Get Happy Be Fit I talk about my struggles with conflict, anxiety and guilt during this time of turmoil and injustice and what I do to safe guard my mental health while supporting the causes I believe in.
.
Mental health and stress management are so important to our overall physical health and longevity. You can’t pour from an empty cup so please take care of yourself.
.
Never be scared to stand up for what is right. I literally lost hundreds of followers last week after my Black Tuesday post. I want to say thank you to all of you who are still here. You make my days brighter and I hope I can do the same for you.
.
Check my story to download Get Happy Be Fit on ITunes or search for it on your favorite podcast platform.
.
And always remember....
.
Your worth has nothing to do with your weight. Love and respect yourself. Enjoy life and be happy.💖

Caption:
[#guestlist] Introducing the parmo, Middlesbrough’s world famous signature dish 🍴 Alex and I were lucky enough to go along to the World Parmo Championships at @middlesbrough_townhall, which made a comeback for 2019! We waited with baited breath to find out which of the four finalists would take the crown, but it was Stockton favourite, Borge, that stole the top title 👑 this used to be one of my picks for birthday meals when I was younger, but I’m definitely long overdue a visit!
•
But what exactly is a parmo? I suppose if you’re not from Teesside, the parmo is a bit of a rarity, so let me explain. Think butterflied chicken breast covered in panko breadcrumbs, fried and topped with bechamel sauce and melted cheese 🍗🧀 they’re so naughty, but soooooo nice! If you’re ever in the area, you should definitely try one 🤤

Caption:
Getting a little emotional lately when I think about how far I’ve come in 2 years. I’d been thinking about getting my MBA since landing in corporate America after my undergrad in theatre and really enjoying it. That’s about 7 years in the workforce, thinking about going to grad school. Two years ago my mom dared me to take the GMAT. She knew what she was doing. Ha. With competition in my top 5 strengths y’all know I had to go for it. With less than a year to go, I know I’m going to make it. I’ve learned so much and feel like the world has opened up even more for me with endless possibilities. So to quote my bestie @adele “hello from the other sideeee”! Go do that thing you’ve been thinking about for years. •

Dried Tomatoes 
Pine nuts
Garlic 
Rucola 
Salt pepper
Balsamic vinegar 
Olive oil 
Parmesan chunks *Roast the nuts in oil free pan *Boil the pasta
*Mix garlic(press it) with  vinegar oil salt and pepper *wash the Rucola * cut the dried tomatoes and put them in a bowl, when the pasta is done, drain it and add it to the tomatoes, add the vinegar mix and stir till combined. Let it cool down
* When it’s cold add the rest of the ingredients and enjoy it with your loved ones and good wine 🍷 *  Mabe with a grilled italian saussage 😋

Caption:
I remember trying to do lunges three years ago and barely being able to bend my knee - much less be able to go all the way down to tap my knee to the ground (as you do in Crossfit). I love the mobility I’ve gained through my fitness journey. I love the awareness of my body and how I feel in each moment. I love how I can sort through difficult problems in my head while running. I love how I can turn my brain off and forget about those things during a yoga class. Once I began thinking of working out as a form of self-care rather than punishment - weight loss became much easier. 🏃🏼‍♀️🧘🏼‍♀️💛

Caption:
Keep exploring📸🚶🏼🌃🇬🇧
Yesterday I've had the pleasure to organise a mini-meetup. Matthew ( @matthewchimeraphotography ), a fellow passionate instagramer from NYC was visiting London, so I thought I'll gather a few of us and we'll go for a spontaneous walk around Canary Wharf district and see what we can photograph. 
We had a lot of fun😀 It was also a good chance to catch up with my London friends👍🏻 Apart from continuing to practice my architectural photography shift lens skills while shooting various angles from street level, "ironically" the night ended up exploring Topmast Point, a old tower block on the Isle of Dogs estate. 20th floor panoramic view provided the right level of closure for the night😉 Soon you all soon again📸
Thank you for coming🙏🏻🙏🏻🙏🏻

Caption:
2019 was a year of finding my INNER STRENGTH!

This year had the highest highs and the lowest lows for me.

I raised Caden by myself this year as daddy had to work out of town.
CJ and I got engaged this year.
Got pregnant this year.
I miscarried this year.
I became an affiliate than athlete for strong physiquez this year.
I got my NASM PT cert this year.
We took our son to Disney world twice this year.
Had to have a biopsy for precancerous cells this year.
Spent a week in Florida and made amazing memories as a family this year.
Went to Vegas with the SP team and met some of the most amazing people this year.
Grew stronger, healthier, and happier this year.

It has been a crazy year but through the lows I found my strength. I’ve gained so much confidence in my abilities as a mother. I’ve gained confidence and strength in my independence. I went through the absolute hardest time of my life this year but found strength and realized I can get through anything with faith and family.

2020 I’m coming for you! It’s a year for getting married, vacations & trips, moving to NC, getting my PT business going and the best thing of them all is being with my two favorite guys every single day! I can’t wait to see what else 2020 brings!

What were some of your highs and lows this year?! Lemme know below⬇️⬇️

Caption:
Thought is real, physical is an illusion #whatdreamsmaycome 
A persons spirit can live on through you if you choose to remember them in the things that you see and the experiences that you have. 
Take this goat for example, she came over to me today, offering her paw and rubbing her head against my hand. I always called Michael a goat and he would always offer a random goat noise in return so this was a special moment for me. 
These are the memories that keep them alive. 
They never really leave. I see Michael in all his favourite animals, in the films that we watched, the food that we ate and, of course, goats, especially the one pictured. 
They may not be here in the physical realm but they are real in our thoughts.

Caption:
Happy Monday Friends!
.
In this week’s episode of Get Happy Be Fit I talk about what lies beneath our tendency to look at others and feel threatened and how learning to appreciate other’s beauty and accomplishments without our own being threatened will set us up for a successful and happy life.
.
It really feels like society tries to pit us against each other by saying one body type is better than another, but we don’t have to engage in it. We can deal with our internal insecurities and choose to see everyone as our equal. We can appreciate other people’s beauty and accomplishments without feeling bad about our own. We all have our preferences of what we find attractive, but media and society shouldn’t be framing what “ideal” is and everyone should be represented and respected.
.
Get Happy Be Fit is available on all podcast platforms or you can check my story for a link to download on ITunes.
.
For coaching inquiries, email me at GetHappyBeFit@gmail.com
.
Always remember...
.
Your worth has nothing to do with your weight. Love and respect yourself. Enjoy life and be happy.💖

I’ve been craving some sunshine lately so throwing it back to a perfect sunny fall day. Sometimes I can’t believe I lived in New England for 9 years with so many dark and cold months! It’s pretty crazy how the human body adapts even to extreme differences (Texas to Boston) 🤣🤷🏼‍♀️🤪 Working on trusting that my brain and body will adapt to working full time and going to school at night. Caption:
✨Freckles poppin thanks to this Florida sun 🌞💁🏽‍♀️ happy Mother’s Day to all my fellow mommy’s out there!✨
👼🏽Today was a bit bittersweet. Spent the day with my hubs and son at the beach yet I couldn’t help and think about our angel baby that we lost almost 2 months ago and that we aren’t getting ready for our child’s arrival. It was the most physically and emotionally painful thing I’ve ever gone through and I don’t wish it on anyone. But mamas are the strongest humans in the world and we can get through anything when we have FAITH! Which is why I named our baby that we lost, Faith. I pray for all the mamas out there that have also lost their babies before they were able to hold and kiss them and the mamas that are struggling to become mamas. I know your pain when you see ultrasound pictures and break down and cry. Or when you see a pregnant person and ask God why your baby wasn’t able to make it and wish they were still here. Im here for you. Also please always be kind as you never know what someone else is going through! And for the ones that sent me nice texts, messages, etc. or just hung out with me to get my mind off things, you are so appreciated 💜👼🏽

Caption:
I am so happy and proud of myself. I'm finally at the point where I can say, wow Beyza, all the work I've done so far is paying off now and I finally have the opportunity to work with big well known companies. 
Everything I have experienced so far through Instagram is only possible with your help and daily support, thanks for everything 🥺♥️
Many think I have a perfect glamour life. But not everything you see here is all I am. I work 40 hours a week like everyone else and have to study for school. Fashion is my passion and I do it as a hobby. The journey so far has not been easy. So many underestimate the work of the influencers. When I was not yet so successful, I always thought, oh the famous successful people have it so easy. But being self-employed is just as hard as a steady job. Many people always ask me how I can stand so free and easy in front of the camera, I tell you how. As a child I was constantly bullied and nobody wanted me in their circle of friends. I was always in a bad mood and didn't know what to do. With time I discovered fashion for myself. First it started with different hijabstyles, then with the sunglasses that covered my big nose, and then I just posted my outfits here and many people liked my style and I was constantly given love and that motivated me so much. My confidence was like 📈. 
And today I have found my own style and inspire hundreds of girls alhamdulillah 🙏🏽I don't want to appeal you and tell you to get your noses done so you look and feel like me, and you’re self confident, no way! This is my personal experience in life and I don't regret it at all. Not only my appearance has changed but also my way of thinking and my attitude towards life. I thank you from the bottom of my heart for the daily love and numerous support. Since everything in my life is going well, old friends want to come back into my life but that will never happen. The train has already left. I don't need anybody. 
Keep snakes away from me, unless they are from Gucci 🐍
In partnership with @eastpak #eastpak #builttoresist #cnnct #sponsored 
📸 @fahimfarooqphotography

The amount of LOVE I have for these TWO is absolutely indescribable! They are the reason I want to be the best ME that I can be. The best WIFE and MOTHER. People ask me what gives me motivation? It is simple. Them. My family. Being the strongest, healthiest, happiest me that I can be means that I can ( God willing) get to watch my son grow up to be an amazing man and not only watch but be cheering him on right next to him. When I was growing up I saw my mom as superwoman. I want my son to think the same of me. I want him to know that he can accomplish anything he puts his mind to and I want to set that example for him, alongside his father! I want to grow old with the love of my life, ceejy peejy! 😝🥰 I will not let myself or them down. Failure isn’t an option. Family > everything

Caption: I just realized I haven\u2019t posted at all in December! My life has been pretty chaotic lately. I moved this month from a house I loved that was filled with memories, good and bad, and into an amazing apartment that\u2019s all mine. I\u2019ve never lived on my own and there have been moments I wondered if I was capable or strong enough to take care of myself. Now I have no doubt that I will not only survive, but will thrive in this new life I\u2019ve begun. I\u2019ve got goals, baby, and I\u2019ve never been more certain that I will meet them. I may have been hiding a bit lately, but I\u2019m not ready to sail to Valinor just yet. Life is a continuous journey of one adventure after another and I\u2019m so ready to start this one. Caption:
Specially over the past 2 years I have realized the value of consistency and persistence...
Success, may come slow sometimes... 
but with persistence it does get us exactly where we aspire to be.

Rabbits jump around and die in about 8-10 years while tortoises walk around slowly and steadily but live for 150 years!
So my dear friends, 
please never feel like your efforts are useless , 
yes , you may need to analyze and tweak your methods 
but we need to be a tortoise that lasts longer not a rabbit who will garner momentary success and get lost in no time. 
We are here for the longer race and the race is only with ourselves ♥️♥️ 
so hold on we will get there ❤️❤️.
.
#rabbitandtortoise #consistency #persistence #holdon #nevergiveup

Caption:
🍗 FAKEAWAY NIGHT 🍗
•
During this whole lockdown, one thing I was really missing was a proper Boro parmo. I usually live in Middlesbrough, but when the government said you should isolate with your partner if you’ve spent considerable time together, I decided it would be best if I lived out my furlough life in the little pit village of Trimdon Colliery. Now, there’s not a lot here, apart from lovely countryside and horses (which are very lovely, don’t get me wrong), so there’s not a chance of a proper parmo 🤷🏻‍♀️
•
Last night, we had a stab at making our own and do you know what? I’m actually so chuffed with the finished results! 🌟😱 we got the chicken nice and crispy, @matt_donnachie ACED the bechamel sauce, and we figured out the grill to get that oozy cheese topping 🤤 they were so freaking good! I’ll admit, it was a messy process, so we probably won’t do this every time a parmo craving strikes, but for an attempt at a FAKEAWAY, I think it was pretty darn good! 🍴
•
I’ll be writing up a whole blog post about how to make this parmo, but we based our recipe on @parmorama’s, so head over and check it out 🥰
•
Are there any foods that you’re missing while in lockdown?

Caption:
Tuesday’s throwback comes courtesy of The Almighty Cod in Seaton Carew 🐟🍟 I’ve been CRAVING a decent plate of fish and chips for so long now, and it’s totally unnecessary because there’s a chippy just down the road, but nothing beats fish and chips by the sea, am I right? 🌊
•
On our trip to The Almighty Cod, me and Matthew both opted for meal deals - cod for me, haddock for Matthew, plus chips, a choice of curry sauce, peas or gravy, bread and butter, and a drink, all for under a tenner! 💸 And as you can see from the photo, the restaurant definitely isn’t shy with portions 🐠🍟 Our fish was crisp on the outside, but super tender and falling apart inside, which was delicious. I didn’t find the batter to be too oily either - just golden with a gorgeous crunch. The chips were piping hot and again, not too oily. They were particularly gorgeous with a bit of salt! As for the curry sauce, this was probably some of the nicest chip shop curry sauce that I’ve had!
•

Caption: Happy Hump Day everybody! What are your goals? I\u2019ve talked a lot about how mine have shifted lately. My focus was being thin for so long that it feels strange not to be trying to weigh as little as possible. Even though I met my previous goals, that mind set did not set me up for success later. This journey is constant. Goals will shift along with our perspectives. Never stop growing. Never stop challenging yourself to be a better you. Let\u2019s support each other! How can I support you? Remember, your worth has nothing to do with your weight. Love and respect yourself. Enjoy life and be happy!
